The flowchart represents the Pong game modules and their interdependencies:

Modules (Nodes):
----------------
	Backend Framework (Fastify with Node.js, Backend): Handles APIs and core logic.
	
	Frontend Framework (Tailwind CSS + TypeScript, Frontend): Displays the game interface.
	
	Database (SQLite, Backend): Stores game data.
	
	Blockchain (Avalanche + Solidity, Backend): Stores tournament scores securely.

Interdependencies (Arrows):
---------------------------
	Backend Framework â†’ Frontend Framework: Provides APIs for the frontend to fetch/display data.
	
	Backend Framework â†’ Database: Uses SQLite to store/retrieve game data.
	
	Backend Framework â†’ Blockchain: Interacts with Avalanche for score storage/retrieval.
	
	Database â†’ Blockchain: Supports Blockchain with auxiliary data (e.g., score metadata).
	
	Frontend Framework â†’ Blockchain: Displays Blockchain-stored scores to users.
	
	Blockchain â†’ Backend Framework: Sends score data back to the backend for processing.


